⚙️ Installation & Setup
1. Prerequisites

Node.js: Recommended version 18.x, 20.x, or 24.x.

Gmail Account: To send notifications from the contact form.

2. Installation

Open your terminal in the vendhan-website directory and run:

code
Bash
download
content_copy
expand_less
npm install express nodemailer dotenv cors
3. Configure Gmail (App Password)

For security, Gmail requires an App Password rather than your primary password:

Go to your Google Account Settings.

Enable 2-Step Verification.

Search for "App Passwords".

Create a new app password (select 'Mail' and 'Other/Custom Name').

Copy the 16-character code.

4. Set up Environment Variables

Create a file named .env in the root folder and paste the following:

code
Env
download
content_copy
expand_less
PORT=3000
EMAIL_USER=vendhaninfotech@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx  # Paste your 16-character code here
RECEIVER_EMAIL=vendhaninfotech@gmail.com
🏃 Running the Project

To start the local development server, run:

code
Bash
download
content_copy
expand_less
node server.js

Once started, access the site at:

Home: http://localhost:3000

Contact: http://localhost:3000/contact.html

📝 Important Notes

Node.js v24 Compatibility: The server.js uses a middleware-based fallback (app.use) for the catch-all route. This is specifically implemented to prevent PathError issues common in Node v24's strict routing library.

Form Fields: The contact form has been updated to remove the "Company Name" field and utilize a text box for the "Subject" field to allow users more flexibility.

Images: Ensure all images (especially logo.png) are placed inside the public/images/ directory for them to load correctly across all pages.

